      • setIpRange

        public abstract SubnetworkInfo.Builder setIpRange(String ipRange)
        Sets the range of internal IPv4 addresses that are owned by this subnetwork. This range must be a CIDR specification, for example: 192.168.0.0/16. Ranges must be unique and non-overlapping within a network.
